definition: to gather/to collect/collected works/classifier for sections of a TV series etc: episode

sentences.english: It was the role in a television series 21 Jump Street .
sentences.chinese: 那是在電視影集《龍虎少年隊》裏的一個角色。

sentences.english: Include a picture of a pregnant woman in collections of photographs and pictures depicting families.
sentences.chinese: 影集裏收放女人懷孕的照片，以及家庭生活的寫真。

sentences.english: China Film Group chooses the 20 titles after screening thousands of options.
sentences.chinese: 中影集團會從數千部影片中最終選出這20部電影。

sentences.english: Your posted slideshows and photos will still display on your webpages.
sentences.chinese: 張貼你的影集和照片，仍然會顯示你的網頁。

sentences.english: He has taken exhibitions and published books of pictures about Italy and Japan.
sentences.chinese: 他舉辦過攝影展，出版過關於意大利和日本的攝影集。

sentences.english: He said they need a new book of photographs.
sentences.chinese: 他說他公司需要一本新的攝影集。

sentences.english: He publishes a book on the former German colonies.
sentences.chinese: 還出版過一部前德國殖民地的攝影集。

sentences.english: She sorted the photos and stuck them in separate allums.
sentences.chinese: 她把照片分了類，貼在不同的影集裏。
我收藏了他所有的影集。

sentences.english: But he applied again, and after viewing his collection of photographs, the school accepted him.
sentences.chinese: 但是他再次申請，校方看了他的攝影集後錄取了他。

sentences.english: SpongeBob SquarePants is an American animated television series .
sentences.chinese: 海綿寶寶是一部美國動畫影集。

definition: photobook (loanword from Japanese), generally sexy portraits of an actress or model
